&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;The area around Batworthy is unusually rich in ancient history, even for Dartmoor. Even though this walk is relatively short, and has only gentle inclines, we&amp;rsquo;ll encounter a lot of bronze age remains, starting with one of the best and largest hut circles on the moor. There&amp;rsquo;s also two tors included, one of which has some very well formed rock basins.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We include some driving directions, although a Satnav will generally find the way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;from-warren-house-inn-towards-moretonhampstead-&#34;&gt;From Warren House Inn (towards Moretonhampstead) &amp;hellip;..
&lt;/h3&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;Take 1st road on LEFT – route to Fernworthy

Pass Jurston Farm

Yellands Crossroads – TURN LEFT

Pass left turn to Lower Corndon

Pass right turn .....

Take HAIRPIN LEFT to Fernworthy - use the layby to turn the car!

Pass a left turn to Higher Corndon

Take RIGHT turn and pass Collihole Farm, Hole Farm and Cullaton to T-junction, turn LEFT toTHORN

Pass THORN and go to YEO FARM

At Yeo Farm bear RIGHT to TEIGNCOMBE

Drive through Teigncombe to the end of the road

The end-of-the-road car park is marked with the yellow cross.
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;parking&#34;&gt;Parking
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;There is a small parking area at the given coordinates. The approach roads to Batworthy are quite long and narrow, although rarely busy.&lt;/p&gt;
